  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Production Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Descriptions:</strong></p><ul><li>Process Optimisation: To ensure efficient operation of all plant and equipment with Production team. To participate and coordinate within Production, with discussions with other Departments involved, ensure process and system adherence is complied according to the required specifications.</li></ul><ul><li>Production Coordination: Responsible for the coordination works for the day-to-day operations of all Production lines and other departments. This includes daily operational aspects of job planning, manpower arrangements, chemical processing, plant equipment and chemical bath maintenance.</li></ul><ul><li>Production Line Upkeep: Be the main point of contact for production supervisors and operators to ensure chemical baths, chemical tanks and other critical equipment are properly maintained within specification and functioning efficiently. Collaborate with technical team to troubleshoot and resolve issues.</li></ul><ul><li>Quality Control: Ensure documentation and procedures are updated and maintained within the Production lines. Assist in troubleshooting works in relation to production adherence to the related documentation and procedures.</li></ul><ul><li>Continuous Improvement: To actively pursue and improve the efficiency of existing processes and procedures, meet technical specifications, seek continuous improvements, and to sustain the company’s internal capacity in order to meet output targets.</li></ul><ul><li>Safety Compliance: To ensure safety regulations and company policies are adhered to within the Production lines. This includes participation in safety meetings and upholding safety standards to maintain a safe working environment in accordance to industry standards.</li></ul><ul><li>Housekeeping: To coordinate with supervisors to ensure good housekeeping (5S), safe working condition, quality of work and proper handling of chemicals and waste disposal of production lines.</li></ul><ul><li>Others: Senior Production Engineer may be delegated with additional duties by the reporting heads. However, such delegation does not relieve his or her overall work responsibilities as stated above.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Engineering or related disciplines. Preferably in relation to Chemistry or Chemical Engineering.</li></ul><p>    Preferred Experience:</p><ul><li>3 - 6 years in Aerospace industry in supervisory positions relating to operations.</li><li>3 - 6 years of chemical processing experience including but not limited to anodizing, electroplating, chemical cleaning, etc.</li></ul><p></p><p></p>",
